title: xml parsing and print json with boost property tree
content:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<person>
    <id>12345</id>
    <name>
        <first>Иван</first>
        <last>Иванов</last>
    </name>
    <age>30</age>
    <address>
        <city>Москва</city>
        <street>Улица Примерная</street>
        <zipcode>12345</zipcode>
    </address>
    <contact>
        <email>ivan.ivanov@example.com</email>
        <phone>
            <mobile>123-456-7890</mobile>
            <home>987-654-3210</home>
        </phone>
    </contact>
</person>

//--------------------------------------- CODE ---------------------------------------------------//
#include <iostream>
#include <boost/property_tree/ptree.hpp>
#include <boost/property_tree/xml_parser.hpp>
#include <boost/property_tree/json_parser.hpp>

#include "boost/chrono.hpp"

int TestXmlRead() {
    boost::chrono::system_clock::time_point start = boost::chrono::system_clock::now();

    boost::property_tree::ptree pt;

    try {
        read_xml("text.xml", pt);

        std::string id = pt.get<std::string>("person.id");
        std::string firstName = pt.get<std::string>("person.name.first");
        std::string lastName = pt.get<std::string>("person.name.last");
        int age = pt.get<int>("person.age");

        std::string city = pt.get<std::string>("person.address.city");
        std::string street = pt.get<std::string>("person.address.street");
        std::string zipcode = pt.get<std::string>("person.address.zipcode");

        std::string email = pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.email");
        std::string mobilePhone = pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.phone.mobile");
        std::string homePhone = pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.phone.home");

        std::cout << "ID: " << id << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Name: " << firstName << " " << lastName << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Age: " << age << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Address: " << street << ", " << city << ", " << zipcode << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Email: " << email << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Mobile Phone: " << mobilePhone << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Home Phone: " << homePhone << std::endl;
    } catch (const std::exception& e) {
        std::cerr << "Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }
    boost::chrono::system_clock::time_point end = boost::chrono::system_clock::now();
    std::cout << "XML READ Elapsed time: " << boost::chrono::duration_cast<boost::chrono::milliseconds>(end - start).count() << "ms" << std::endl;

    return 0;
}

int TestXmlWrite() {
    boost::chrono::system_clock::time_point start = boost::chrono::system_clock::now();

    boost::property_tree::ptree pt;
    try{
        read_xml("text.xml", pt);

        boost::property_tree::ptree jsonPt;
        jsonPt.put("id", pt.get<std::string>("person.id"));
        jsonPt.put("name.first", pt.get<std::string>("person.name.first"));
        jsonPt.put("name.last", pt.get<std::string>("person.name.last"));
        jsonPt.put("age", pt.get<int>("person.age"));

        jsonPt.put("address.city", pt.get<std::string>("person.address.city"));
        jsonPt.put("address.street", pt.get<std::string>("person.address.street"));
        jsonPt.put("address.zipcode", pt.get<std::string>("person.address.zipcode"));

        jsonPt.put("contact.email", pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.email"));
        jsonPt.put("contact.phone.mobile", pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.phone.mobile"));
        jsonPt.put("contact.phone.home", pt.get<std::string>("person.contact.phone.home"));

        boost::property_tree::json_parser::write_json("out.json", jsonPt);
    } catch (const std::exception& e) {
        std::cerr << "Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }
    boost::chrono::system_clock::time_point end = boost::chrono::system_clock::now();
    std::cout << "JSON WRITE Elapsed time: " << boost::chrono::duration_cast<boost::chrono::milliseconds>(end - start).count() << "ms" << std::endl;

return 0;
}

int main() {
    TestXmlRead();
    TestXmlWrite();
    return 0;
}

import pandas as pd
import sqlalchemy as sa

df = pd.DataFrame([{'name_county': "Santa Bárbara d'Oeste'"}])

engine = sa.create_engine('sqlite://', echo=True)
tbl = sa.Table('t', sa.MetaData(), sa.Column('name_county', sa.String))
tbl.create(engine)

with engine.begin() as conn:
    q = """INSERT INTO t (name_county) VALUES (:name_county)"""
    for row in df.itertuples():
            conn.execute(sa.text(q), [{'name_county': row.name_county}])

--Turtle Diggy Hole
--------FUNCTIONS---------
 
--size setup
 
function setup()   
    term.write("Length: ")
    len = tonumber(read())
    term.write("Width: ")
    wid = tonumber(read())
    term.write("Depth: ")
    dep = tonumber(read())

    if ((wid % 2 == 1 and dep % 2 == 1)) then
        travel = len - 1
        lenAway = true
    end
    if dep%2 == 1 then
        travel = travel + wid - 1
        widAway = true
    end
    travel = travel + dep -1

    if len * wid * dep + travel - 1 >= fuel then
        willrun = false
    end
end
 
--digs across length 
 
function length()
    count = count + 1
    for i=2,len do
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.forward()
    end
end
 
--left turn
 
function TurnLeft()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    turtle.dig()
    turtle.forward()
    turtle.turnLeft()
end
 
--right turn
 
function TurnRight()
    turtle.turnRight()
    turtle.dig()
    turtle.forward()
    turtle.turnRight()
end
 
--determines turn
 
function pick()
    eo = count % 2
    if eo == 1 then
        TurnRight()
    elseif eo == 0 then
        TurnLeft()
    end
end

function down()
    count = (wid)%2
    turtle.digDown()
    turtle.down()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    deep = deep + 1
end

function recall()
    if dep ~= 1 then
        for i = 2, dep do
            turtle.up()
        end
    end 

    if lenAway then
        for i = 2, len do
            turtle.back()
        end
    end

    if widAway then
        turtle.turnLeft()
        for i = 2, wid do
            turtle.forward()
        end
        turtle.turnRight()
    end
end

function mine()
    for i = 1, dep do
        for i=1,wid do
            length()
            if i ~= wid then
            	pick()
            end
        end
        if deep ~= dep then
            down()
        end
    end
    
    
end
 
----------GLOBAL----------
 
len = 0
wid = 0
dep = 0
deep = 1
count = 0
fuel = turtle.getFuelLevel()
travel = 0
willrun = true
widAway = false
lenAway = false
 
-----------MAIN-----------
 
setup()
if willrun then
    mine()
    recall()
else
    print("Not enough fuel!")
end

local tables = {useId, shovelId, ropeId, macheteId, scytheId}
local settings = storage.extras
local movementHistory = {}
storage.vithraxFollow = storage.vithraxFollow or ''

-- functions
local function useAll()
    local tiles = getNearTiles(pos())
    table.insert(tiles, g_map.getTile(pos()))

    for _, tile in ipairs(tiles) do
        for __, item in ipairs(tile:getItems()) do
            local id = item:getId()
            for i, array in ipairs(tables) do
                if array[id] then
                    if i == 1 then
                        use(item)
                    elseif i == 2 then
                        useWith(settings.shovel, item)
                    elseif i == 3 then
                        useWith(settings.rope, item) 
                    elseif i == 4 then
                        useWith(settings.machete, item)
                    else
                        useWith(settings.scythe, item)
                    end
                    return true
                end
            end
        end
    end

    return false
end

setDefaultTab("KT")

local getOutfit = player:getOutfit()
local playerOutfit = { 
    type = getOutfit.type, 
    head = getOutfit.head, 
    body = getOutfit.body, 
    legs = getOutfit.legs, 
    feet = getOutfit.feet, 
    addons = getOutfit.addons, 
    --mount = getOutfit.mount
}

local followIcon = addIcon("holdFollow",  {outfit=playerOutfit, movable=true, text = "Follow"},
macro(75, "[Melee] Close Follow", function(macro)
    local target = getCreatureByName(storage.vithraxFollow)
    local tpos = target and target:getPosition()
    if tpos and getDistanceBetween(tpos,pos()) < 2 then
        movementHistory = {}
        return
    end
    local dest = movementHistory[posz()]
    if tpos and not dest then
        local path = findPath(tpos, pos(), 20, { ignoreNonPathable = true, precision = 1 })
        if path then
            dest = tpos
        end
    end
    if not dest then
        if useAll() then
            return
        end
        delay(100)
    end
    if dest and getDistanceBetween(dest, pos()) == 0 then
        delay(100)
        useAll()
        return
    end
    local path = findPath(pos(), dest, 20, { ignoreNonPathable = true, precision = 1 })
    if not path then
        useAll()
        delay(100)
        return
    end
    CaveBot.walkTo(dest, 20, { ignoreNonPathable = true, precision = target and 1 or 0 })
end))

UI.TextEdit(storage.vithraxFollow or 'Player Name', function(widget, newText)
    storage.vithraxFollow = newText
end)

onCreaturePositionChange(function(creature, oldPos, newPos)
    if not newPos then return end
    if creature:getName():lower() ~= storage.vithraxFollow:lower():trim() then return end

    -- register position on current floor
    movementHistory[newPos.z] = newPos
end)
UI.Separator()

followIcon:setSize({height=55,width=50})
followIcon.text:setFont('verdana-11px-rounded')
followIcon.text:setTextOffset({x = 12, y = -8})

from itertools import combinations

from sqlalchemy import INTEGER, String, create_engine
from sqlalchemy.orm import DeclarativeBase, Mapped, Session, mapped_column


class Base(DeclarativeBase):
    pass


class Record(Base):
    __tablename__ = "record"

    id: Mapped[int] = mapped_column(INTEGER, autoincrement=True, primary_key=True)
    value: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(String)

    def __repr__(self) -> str:
        return f"Record(values={self.value!r})"


if __name__ == "__main__":
    points = ["B", "C", "D", "E", "F", "G", "H"]
    combination_list = combinations(points, 3)

    engine = create_engine("sqlite:///./test.sqlite", echo=True)
    Base.metadata.create_all(engine)
    with Session(engine) as session:
        result = []
        for combination in combination_list:
            result.append(Record(value=str(["A"] + list(combination) + ["I", 1, 100])))
            result.append(Record(value=str(["A"] + list(combination) + ["I", 1, 160])))
            result.append(Record(value=str(["A"] + list(combination) + ["I", 2, 100])))
            result.append(Record(value=str(["A"] + list(combination) + ["I", 2, 160])))
        print(result)
        session.add_all(result)
        session.commit()

<?php

namespace App\Services\Intergrations;

use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Config;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Http;


class ConfigService
{

    private $configEndpoint;
    private $headers = [];
    private $queryParameters = [];
    private $authType;
    private $authToken;
    private $authUsername;
    private $authPassword;
    private $responseTimeout = 10; //seconds
    private $requestTimeout = 5; //seconds
    private $retryCount = 3; //count
    private $retryDelay = 500; //milliseconds


    public function __construct($configName)
    {
        $this->init();
    }


    /**
     * Set a custom header for the request
     * @param string $header
     * @param string $value
     * @param boolean $writeProtect if true, stops the header from being overwritten
     * @return ConfigService
     */
    public function setHeader(string $header, string $value, bool $writeProtect = false) : ConfigService
    {
        if(!$writeProtect && !array_key_exists($header, $this->headers)) {
            $this->headers[ $header ] = $value;
        }

        return $this;
    }


    /**
     * set the query parameters for the request
     *
     * @param string $param
     * @param string $value
     * @param boolean $writeProtect
     * @return ConfigService
     */
    public function setQueryParameter(string $param, string $value, bool $writeProtect = false) : ConfigService
    {
        if(!$writeProtect && !array_key_exists($param, $this->queryParameters)) {
            $this->queryParameters[ $param ] = $value;
        }

        return $this;
    }


    /**
     * Set the auth for the request
     *
     * @param string $token
     * @param string $tokenOrUsername token || username
     * @param string $password
     * @return ConfigService
     */
    public function setAuth(string $type, string $tokenOrUsername = null, string $password = null) : ConfigService
    {
        $this->authToken = null;
        $this->authUsername = null;
        $this->authPassword = null;

        if(in_array($type, ['token', 'basic'])) {
            $this->authType = $type;
        }

        if($type == 'basic') {
            $this->authUsername = $tokenOrUsername;
            $this->authPassword = $password;
        }
        else if($type == 'token') {
            $this->authToken = $tokenOrUsername;
        }

        return $this;
    }


    /**
     * Alias of setGenericSetting
     * Set the response timeout in seconds
     *
     * @param integer $timeout
     * @return ConfigService
     */
    public function setResponseTimeout(int $timeout) : ConfigService
    {
        $this->setGenericSetting('responseTimeout', $timeout);
        return $this;
    }


    /**
     * Alias of setGenericSetting
     * Set the request (connection) timeout in seconds
     *
     * @param integer $timeout
     * @return ConfigService
     */
    public function setRequestTimeout(int $timeout) : ConfigService
    {
        $this->setGenericSetting('requestTimeout', $timeout);
        return $this;
    }


    /**
     * Alias of setGenericSetting
     * the retry count (how many times to retry the request)
     *
     * @param integer $timeout
     * @return ConfigService
     */
    public function setRetryCount(int $count) : ConfigService
    {
        $this->setGenericSetting('retryCount', $count);
        return $this;
    }


    /**
     * Alias of setGenericSetting
     * Set the retry delay in milliseconds
     *
     * @param integer $timeout
     * @return ConfigService
     */
    public function setRetryDelay(int $delay) : ConfigService
    {
        $this->setGenericSetting('retryDelay', $delay);
        return $this;
    }


    /**
     * Override the default endpoint
     *
     * @param string $domain
     * @param string $uri
     * @return ConfigService
     */
    public function setEndpoint(string $domain, string $uri) : ConfigService
    {
        $configDomain = $domain;
        $configUri = $uri;
        $configUrl = $this->formatUrl($configDomain, $configUri);
        $this->configEndpoint = $configUrl;
        return $this;
    }


    /**
     * Setup some default values
     *
     * @return void
     */
    private function init()
    {
        $configDomain = Config::get('services.intergrations.config_domain');
        $configUri = Config::get('services.intergrations.config_uri');
        $configUrl = $this->formatUrl($configDomain, $configUri);
        $this->configEndpoint = $configUrl;
    }


    /**
     * Set some generic setting (see alias methods)
     *
     * @return array
     */
    private function setGenericSetting($setting, $value)
    {
        $this->{$setting} = $value;
    }


    /**
     * Make the call and Get the config
     *
     * @return mixed
     */
    public function get()
    {

        $http = Http::withHeaders($this->headers)
            ->timeout($this->responseTimeout)
            ->connectTimeout($this->requestTimeout)
            ->retry($this->retryCount, $this->retryDelay);

        if($this->authType) {
            match($this->authType) {
                'token' => $http->withToken($this->authToken),
                'basic' => $http->withBasicAuth($this->authUsername, $this->authPassword),
            };
        }

        $response = $http->get($this->configEndpoint);


        if($response->failed() || $response->clientError() || $response->serverError()) {
            throw new \Exception('Failed to get config from ' . $this->configEndpoint . ' - ' . $response->status() . ' - ' . $response->json());
        }


        return $response->json();

    }


    /**
     * Helper method for making sure we have a valid formatted URL
     *
     * @param string ...$urlParts
     * @return string
     */
    private function formatUrl(string ...$urlParts) : string
    {
        $url = '';
        foreach($urlParts as $part)
        {
            if(substr($part, -1) != '/') {
                $part .= '/';
            }

            if(substr($part, 0, 1) == '/') {
                $part = substr($part, 1);
            }

            $url .= $part;
        }
        return $url;
    }

}
